rience and also looks beyond Japan to explore pre-modern book history, practices of preaching, miracles of reading, and the Mahayana Buddhist "cult of the book."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aBooks and readingxReligious aspectsxBuddhism. 0aBuddhismxHistoryx1185-1600xJapan. 0aBuddhismzJapanxHistoryy1185-1600. 0aBuddhist literature, JapanesexHistory and criticism. 0aFolk literature, JapanesexHistory and criticism. 0aMovement, Psychology ofxReligious aspectsxBuddhism. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520947894423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520947894.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles